      We say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>étale</fr:em> at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is both flat and unramified at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>.
      We say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is étale if it is étale at all points.
      We say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is étale at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>, or that it is a <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>-prescheme which is étale at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> etc.
    </html:li>

    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;b. &quot;">
      Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> be a local homomorphism.
      We say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is étale, or that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is étale over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is flat and unramified over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>
