type="user">sga1-i.4.9</fr:addr><fr:route>sga1-i.4.9.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>I.4.9</fr:number><fr:parent>sga1-i.4</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We say that a cover of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> is étale (resp. unramified) if it is a <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>-scheme <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> that is finite over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> and étale (resp. unramified) over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>The first condition means that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is defined by a coherent sheaf of algebras <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>.
  The second means that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}]]></fr:tex> is locally free over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> (resp. means absolutely nothing) <fr:em>and</fr:em>, further, that, for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  Y]]></fr:tex>, the fibre <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}(y)=\mathcal {B}_y\otimes _{\mathcal {O}_y}k(y)]]></fr:tex> is a separable algebra (i.e. a finite composition of finite separable extensions) over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k(y)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:tree
